    "body": "```ruby\r\nmarkdown.render('## tl;dr')\r\n=> \"<h2 id=\\\"tl-dr\\\">tl;dr</h2>\\n\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nPer [this answer](http://stackoverflow.com/a/38507669/1825390), punctuation is stripped from the anchor. I've confirmed GH processes it this way [here](https://gist.github.com/xavdid/1395d979457ce2e0babb1106888072c0#tldr). So, the resulting id of the above code should be `tldr`. I believe the `;` is getting erroneously replace with a space. \r\n\r\nThanks a bunch!"
