    "body": "Given this markdown\r\n\r\n```markdown\r\nNow tell `rvm` to use the new default by running\r\n`` `\r\nrvm --default use 2.3.3\r\n`` `\r\n```\r\n This will generate the html\r\n```html\r\n<p>Now tell <code>rvm</code> to use the new default by running</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  <code>rvm --default use 2.3.3</code>\r\n</p>\r\n```\r\n\r\nNow in order to style these differently I can't differentiate what is inline code or a block of code.\r\nIt would be good to be able to add a class to be able to select them differently e.g.\r\n```markdown\r\n`rvm`\r\n```\r\nbecomes\r\n```html\r\n<code class=\"inline-code\">rvm</code>\r\n```\r\n\r\nand\r\n\r\n```markdown\r\n`` `\r\nrvm --default use 2.3.3\r\n`` `\r\n```\r\nbecomes\r\n```html\r\n<p>\r\n  <code class=\"block-code\">rvm --default use 2.3.3</code>\r\n</p>\r\n```"
