    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "In the docs, you write that \"The `Redcarpet::Markdown` object is encouraged to be instantiated once with the required settings, and reused between parses.\"\r\n\r\nWould it be possible to provide an example of best practices for this? Currently my app has a method in the application_helper.rb like so:\r\n\r\n```ruby\r\ndef render_markdown(text)\r\n  Redcarpet::Markdown.new(Redcarpet::Render::HTML).render(text).html_safe\r\nend\r\n```\r\n\r\nIs this instantiating a new renderer every time it’s called (multiple times per pageview)? Is there a better way of going about this – say, by defining a constant in the app initializer?\r\n\r\nI’m curious for my own case, and it might be helpful to add any relevant best practices to the documentation as well."
