    "body": "Hi, I am working on a project which needs a form of file transclusion[1] implemented. \r\n\r\nIn short, the syntax I wanted to add to the parser would be similar to inline links: ```:[name](path/to/markdown.md)``` - thre's an extra colon in first position -  inspired by one of the comments in the commonmark discussion [2]. \r\n\r\nI want to add this feature but I couldn't find any obvious way of injecting my logic into the parser - especially since there's a specific comment regarding monkey patching. Is there something I'm missing, or am I approaching the problem the wrong way?\r\n\r\n[1] https://talk.commonmark.org/t/transclusion-or-including-sub-documents-for-reuse/270\r\n[2] https://talk.commonmark.org/t/transclusion-or-including-sub-documents-for-reuse/270/7"
